definitions: Produced (books, newspapers, etc.) by means of a mechanical process involving the transfer of text or designs to paper.
Marked (a surface) with a design or pattern by means of printing.
Wrote (text) clearly without joining the letters.
Produced a hard copy of (data or text stored on a computer) using a printer.
examples: The company printed a million copies of the book.
The fabric was printed with a floral design.
She printed her name at the top of the form.
He printed the document from his laptop.
